​

​', 2);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (6, 4, 'Week 4', '', 'Week  four of fishing league brought 24 walleyes to the scale for 55.0625 lbs.  First place went to Steve Dahle and Jamie Jahn who weighed 3 fish for 12.5625 lbs., including the big fish of the night an 6.3125 lber.  Second Place was Mikkal Erickson and Logan Spray weighing 2 fish for 9.4375 lbs.  Third Place went to Sam Thomas and Scott Van Overbeke who weighed 3 fish for 7.5 lbs.    Fourth Place went to Eric and Adam Spray who weighed 2 fish for 4.375 lbs.  Fifth Place was Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz weighing 2 fish for 4.125 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Matt Fischer and Jeff Reike who weighed 2 fish for 3.375 lbs.​​ ​

​', 3);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (6, 5, 'Week 5', '', '​​ ​

Week  five of fishing league saw 47  walleyes brought to the scale for 103.75 lbs.  First place went to Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz who weighed 5 fish for 15.125 lbs.Second Place was Mikkal Erickson and Logan Spray weighing 4 fish for 11.1875 lbs.  Third Place went to Corey Joyce and Sub (Chris Joyce) who weighed 2 fish for 9.5 lbs.    Fourth Place went to Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson who weighed 2 fish for 8.5 lbs, including the big fish of the night a 6.5 lber.  Fifth Place was Eric and Adam Spray weighing 4 fish for 7.1875 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Dean Broin and Jerod Zimbelman who weighed 2 fish for 6.5 lbs.​​ ​', 4);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (6, 6, 'Week 6', '', 'Week  six of fishing league saw only 18 walleyes brought to the scale for 39.125 lbs.  First place went to Josh Weckwerth and Trent Weckwerth who weighed 5 fish for 10.3125 lbs.Second Place was Eric Spray and Adam Spray weighing 4 fish for 8.25 lbs.  Third Place went to Dean Broin and Jerod Zimbelman who weighed 1 fish for 4.0 lbs, this was also the big fish of the night.  Fourth Place went to Jack Anderson and Tony Meseck who weighed 2 fish for 3.5625 lbs.  Fifth Place was Trent Jorgenson and Matt Norby weighing 1 fish for 3.125 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was a tie between Sam Thomas and Scott Van Overbeke weighing 2 fish for 2.5 lbs and Nate and Robb Gilkey weighing 1 fish for 2.5 lbs.

Next week will be the conclusion of fishing league for 2021.

**​', 5);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (6, 7, 'Week 7', '', 'Week seven of fishing league saw 22 walleyes brought to the scale for 57.7 lbs.  First place went to Jack Anderson and Tony Meseck who weighed 5 fish for 9.25 lbs.Second Place was Tom Halvorson and (sub) Larry Halvorson who weighed 2 fish for 8.4375 lbs.  Third Place went to Steve Dahle and Jamie Jahn who weighed 2 fish for 8.0 lbs, they also had the big fish of the night, a 7.0625 lber.  Fourth Place went to Dean Broin and Jerod Zimbelman who weighed 2 fish for 6.5 lbs.  Fifth Place was Trent Jorgenson and Matt Norby weighing 1 fish for 6.125 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson weighing 2 fish for 4.375 lbs.

**​', 6);
INSERT INTO league_photos (league_id, url, sort_order) VALUES (6, '/images/tournaments/img-3021_1.jpg', 0);

-- League 2020
UPDATE fishing_league SET roster = '', end_of_year_results = 'End of the Year Results

This year''s fishing league was cut short to 5 weeks due to inclement weather.  There were 139 walleyes weighed for 336.75 lbs, a 2.4 lb average.

Top honors went to Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson with 27.625 lbs.  Second place went to Eric Spray and Adam Spray with 22.9375 lbs.  Third place was Corey Heinrich and Jerry Heinrich with 21.0 lbs.  Congratulations too the top three place winners and to all the other teams who fished this year.

​

_[2020 Lac Qui Parle Lake Walleye League Results](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nMW_ATY0gLLjVN3FcxWzpMxPCHZJJBeZhokX57KRQWM/edit#gid=0)_', show_gallery = 0 WHERE id = 7;
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (7, 1, 'Week 1', '', 'The first week of fishing league saw 24 walleyes brought to the scales for a total of 69.3 lbs.  Big fish of the night went to Steve Dahle/Jamie Jahn a 10.25 lber.  First place was Jerry Heinrich/Corey Heinrich who weighed 5 fish for 12.375 lbs.  Second place went to Jon Jerve/Tony Ohmacht who weighed 2 fish for 10.75 lbs.  Third place was Steve Dahle/Jamie Jahn who weighed one fish for 10.25 lbs.  Fourth place was Nate Gilkey/Robb Gilkey who weighed 3 fish for 8.1875 lbs.  Fifth place went to Jeff Randall/Cody Thompson who weighed 2 fish for 5.1875 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Josh Weckwerth/Trent Weckwerth who weighed 2 fish for 4.9375 lbs.

​', 0);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (7, 2, 'Week 2', '', 'The second week of fishing league saw 18  walleyes brought to the scales for a total of 38.375 lbs.  Big fish of the night went to Darin Lund/Jay Kleven with a 4.125 lber.  First place was Chad Jordahl/Ben George who weighed 2 fish for 6.5 lbs.  Second place went to Pete McGinty/Shannon Larson who weighed 3 fish for 5.6875 lbs.  Third place was Sam Thomas/Scott VanOverbeke who weighed 2 fish for 5.5 lbs.  Fourth place was Corey Joyce/Steve Benson who weighed 4 fish for 5.25 lbs.  Fifth place went to Darin Lund/Jay Kleven who weighed 1 fish for 4.125 lbs, this was also the big fish of the night.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Steve Dahle/Jamie Jahn who weighed 1 fish for 3.9375 lbs.

​', 1);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (7, 3, 'Week 3', '', '​

The third week of fishing league saw 27  walleyes brought to the scales for a total of 71.0625 lbs.  Big fish pot of the night went to Jeff Reuss/Janie Pring with a 4.5625lber.  First place was Eric Spray/Adam Spray who weighed 4 fish for 12.375 lbs.  Second place went to Andy Niemeyer/Shane Stavne who weighed 1 fish for 6.75 lbs.  Third place was Pete McGinty/Shannon Larson who weighed 3 fish for 5.9375 lbs.  Fourth place was Jeff Reuss/Janie Pring who weighed 2 fish for 5.5625 lbs.  Fifth place went to Nate Gilkey/Robb Gilkey who weighed 2 fish for 5.125 lbs. Rounding out the top 6 places was Jack Anderson/Tony Meseck who weighed 1 fish for 5.0625lbs.

​', 2);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (7, 4, 'Week 4', '', '​​ ​

After having two weeks off to poor weather conditions, the fourth week of fishing league saw 39  walleyes brought to the scales for a total of 80.625 lbs.  Big fish pot of the night went to Tom Ludvigson/Dustin Fernholz with a 3.75lber.  First place was Adam Niemeyer/Shane Stavne who weighed 4 fish for 7.0625 lbs.  Second place went to Trent Jorgenson/Matt Norby who weighed 3 fish for 6.375 lbs.  Third place was Eric Spray/Adam Spray who weighed 3 fish for 6.0625 lbs.  Fourth place was Cody Enger/Sean Hauck who weighed 4 fish for 6.0 lbs.  Fifth place went to Pete McGinty/Shannon Larson who weighed 3 fish for 5.9375 lbs. Rounding out the top 6 places was Matt Fischer/Jeff Reike who weighed 2 fish for 5.6875 lbs.

​', 3);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (7, 5, 'Week 5', '', '​​ ​

The final week of fishing league saw 31 walleyes brought to the scales for a total of 77.375 lbs.  Big fish pot of the night went to Pete McGinty/Shannon Larson with a 7.875 lber.  First place was Corey Reiffenberger/Gracyn/Lainey who weighed 5 fish for 14.5 lbs.  Second place went to Trent Jorgenson/Matt Norby who weighed 5 fish for 11.5 lbs.  Third place was Pete McGinty/Shannon Larson who weighed 2 fish for 10.0625 lbs.  Fourth place was Corey Joyce/Steve Benson who weighed 5 fish for 8.8125 lbs.  Fifth place went to Tom Ludvigson/Dustin Fernholz who weighed 2 fish for 6.1875 lbs. Rounding out the top 6 places was Josh Weckwerth/Trent Weckwerth who weighed 2 fish for 3.875 lbs.', 4);

-- League 2019
UPDATE fishing_league SET roster = '', end_of_year_results = 'End of the Year Results

A total of 164 walleyes for 487.625 lbs were brought to the scales in 2019.  Top honors went to Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz with 45.4375  lbs.  Second place went to Corey Joyce and Steve Benson with 42.1875 lbs.  Third place was Eric Spray and Adam Spray with 40.625 lbs.  Congratulations too the top three place winners and to all the other teams who fished this year.

​

![Picture](/images/tournaments/img-0324_orig.jpg)

_[2019 Lac Qui Parle Lake Walleye League Results](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1sOdfWjYSXYmUPnXD0Z03NtNVyRncvp1KUddvoAMJpl4/edit#gid=0)_', show_gallery = 1 WHERE id = 8;
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (8, 1, 'Week 1', '', 'The first night of league saw 50 walleyes brought to the scales for a total of 188 lbs.  Corey Joyce and Steve Benson took top honors with 4 fish for 18.875 lbs.  Second place went to Jon Jerve and Tony Ohmacht who weighed 5 fish for 16.9375 lbs.  Third place was Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz who weighed 3 fish for 16.815 lbs.  Fourth Place was Trent Jorgenson and Matt Norby with 5 fish for 16.0 lbs.  Fifth place was Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson who weighed 3 fish for 15.1875 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Jacob Wente and Brennen Longnecker weighing 3 fish for 14.375 lbs.  Big walleye of the night went to Tom Halvorson and Gage Halvorson an 11.3125 lber.​**

**​', 0);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (8, 2, 'Week 2', '', 'The second night of fishing league produced 19 fish for 78.875 lbs.  Corey Heinrich and (sub) Brian Hanson took first place with 3 fish for 17.125 lbs.  Second place was Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson with 4 fish for 15.875 lbs.  Third place was Tom Halvorson and Gage Halvorson with 1 fish for 9.3125 lbs.  This was also the second week in a row team Halvorson took big fish honors.  Fourth place was Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz who weighed 3 fish for 8.375 lbs.  Fifth place went to Steve Dahle and Jamie Jahn with 1 fish for 7.625 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Corey Reiffenberger and Jack Anderson with 2 fish for 5.625lbs.**

​', 1);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (8, 3, 'Week 3', '', '​

**The third night of fishing league saw 17 walleyes brought to the scale for 50 lbs.  Corey Joyce and Steve Benson took first place with 1 fish for 8.3125 lbs and also big fish honors for the night.  Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz took second place with 3 fish for 8.125 lbs.  Third place went to Cody Enger and Sean Hauck with 1 fish for 6.5 lbs.  Fourth Place was Eric Spray and Adam Spray with 3 fish for 6.4375 lbs.  Fifth place was Matt Fischer and Jeff Reike with 2 fish for 5.3125 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Josh Weckwerth and Trent Weckwerth with 2 fish for 4.25 lbs. **​****

****​****

​', 2);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (8, 4, 'Week 4', '', '​​

​

**The fourth night of fishing league saw 15 walleyes brought to the scale for 43.6875 lbs.   Eric and Adam Spray took first place with  2 fish for  12.875 lbs, they were not in the big fish pot. Trent Jorgenson and Matt Norby  took second place with 3 fish for 7.0 lbs.  Third place went to Tom Ludvigson and Dustin Fernholz with 1 fish for 5.875 lbs, this was big fish of the night.  Fourth Place was Matt Fischer and Jeff Reike with 2 fish for 4.625 lbs.  Fifth place was Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson with  2 fish for  3.75 lbs.  Rounding out the top 6 places was Brennen Longnecker and Jacob Wente with 1 fish for  3.3125 lbs. **​****

**​', 3);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (8, 5, 'Week 5', '', 'The fifth night of fishing league saw 4 walleyes brought to the scale for  14.5625 lbs.  Cody Enger and Sean Hauck took first place with 1  fish for  6.875 lbs, this was also big fish for the night.  Corey Joyce and Steve Benson took second place with  1 fish for 4 lbs.  Third place went to  Tony Malmquist and Jordan Fischer with 1 fish for 2.1875 lbs.  Fourth Place was Eric Spray and Adam Spray 1 with fish for 1.5 lbs.', 4);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (8, 6, 'Week 6', '', 'The sixth night of fishing league saw  37 walleyes brought to the scale for 93.5 lbs.  Jamie Jahn and Steve Dahle took first place with 5 fish for  14.0625lbs.    Sam Thomas and Scott VanOverbeck took second place with  4 fish for  13.9375 lbs.  Third place went to Jack Anderson and Corey Reiffenberger with  2 fish for  9.9375 lbs.  Fourth Place was  Trent Jorgenson and Matt Norby with 5 fish for 9.625 lbs.  Jacob Wente and Brennen Longnecker took fifth place with 3 fish for 7.6875 lbs.  Rounding out the top six were Mikkal Erickson and Logan Spray with 5 fish for 7.375 lbs.  Next week is the last week of fishing league and it looks to be a tight race for the top 3 places.', 5);
INSERT INTO league_weeks (league_id, week_number, title, date, content, sort_order) VALUES (8, 7, 'Week 7', '', 'The final night of fishing league saw 22 walleyes brought to the scale for 50.4375 lbs.   Jeff Randall and  Ken Nelson took first place with 2 fish for 6.4375 lbs.  Dave Cornelius and Gary Roder took second place with 2 fish for 5.8125 lbs.  Third place went to  Jon Jerve and  Tony Omacht with 2 fish for 5.75 lbs.  Fourth Place was Jack Anderson and  Corey Reiffenberger with 3 fish for 4.625 lbs.  Corey Joyce and Steve Benson took fifth place with 2 fish for 4.25 lbs.  Rounding out the top six were Trent Jorgenson and Matt Norby with 1 fish for 3.9375 lbs.', 6);
INSERT INTO league_photos (league_id, url, sort_order) VALUES (8, '/images/tournaments/img-0324_orig.jpg', 0);

-- League 2018
UPDATE fishing_league SET roster = '', end_of_year_results = 'End of the Year Results

This year''s fishing league was definitely a tough bite for all anglers.  Pete McGinty and Shannon Larson took 1st Place with 28.6875 lbs.  Tom Ludvigson and Brent Zupan finished in 2nd Place with 22.5625 lbs.  Eric and Adam Spray finished in 3rd Place with 20.625 lbs.  Congratulations too the top three teams and to all the other teams who caught fished a tough bite for 7 weeks.

​

